rComments: I wish Peever taught other classes, because wow this class was amazing. The material can get kinda bland, but expected for a physiology/neurobiology course. But Peever is AMAZING at explaining the concepts and highlights certain things you 100% must know for the exams. Grading is fair, watch out for single word changes in M/C and T/F questions

Super funny, engaging lecturer. Tells you which concept/ slides to focus on for midterm and exam. There were 2 in-class assignments, both were pretty stressful but marked pretty easily by the TAs. Finding past midterms and exams are key as he reuses the same questions. It's also important to know what types/ format of questions he asks.

Very funny prof and clearly explains concepts although sometimes spends too much time on small concepts. Make sure you read his test questions carefully because he often changes small details (especially in the T/F questions).

Dr. Peever was witty, easy to follow and refreshingly focused on actual research rather than textbook drivel. Definitely left that class with many skills UofT is failing to teach all the thousands of undergrads they take in. Wish he taught other classes.
Amazing lecturer, he was really funny and clearly knew the material. Occasionally talked too much and dragged small concepts out. Easy class, would 100% take again if I could!
He doesn't post to the old exams repository. 'Nuff said.

Completely unknowledgable and devoid of teaching skill, but condescending toward students who ask critical questions. Uses his authority and "status" as a professor to dismiss student concerns despite the fact that he is blatantly incorrect or simply doesn't know what he's talking about. His slides are stolen from old profs, but he takes credit.
Found him quite approachable and helpful, tests were fair if you were well prepared.  Enjoyed the material, great class.
Really rude when approached for help outside the class.
worst proff at uft. they should get a new one for his section. cudnt stand him after 1st lecture so i stopped going. really needs to pay attention to students then talk abt his life.

i agree below. he's not good in his lectures sometimes he doesn't make sense, and relates things that don't make sense. he stutters a lot and repeats the same thing and ummms a lot. he's confusing at times, he's lab are long and unnecessary. 3hr lab and we did work for 20 mins. waste of time.

He's seems like a good professor and all but he can be a jerk sometimes on my experiences and he takes pride in "yelling at students" when it comes to problems. I did not have a good conversation with him, but as a lecturer he is alright. I highly recommend to watch out because in class he's nice and all but when you go to him later, he gets rude!
Great first time teacher, more organised and prepared than most long term zoo staff teachers. great speaker.
His notes are very helpful and I love him for takin the time out to make these notes. This way, the student can actually listen in the class without having to rush to take notes.
He's a really nice guy, his notes are super clear, and the material is really easy.
